<item>
            <title>[POOL-135] _numActive &gt; _maxActive under load</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-135</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Whilst investigating other POOL issues, I noticed that _numActive can be &amp;gt; _maxActive when under load. Test case and fix to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12425389">POOL-135</key>
            <summary>_numActive &gt; _maxActive under load</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="markt">Mark Thomas</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="markt">Mark Thomas</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 13 May 2009 22:38:03 +0000</created>
                <updated>Fri, 19 Jun 2009 16:10:48 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 13 May 2009 22:48:40 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.4</version>
                                    <fixVersion>1.5</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12709285" author="markt" created="Thu, 14 May 2009 06:35:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue here is that addobjectToPool() returns an object to the pool and that another thread can borrow the newly returned object before _numActive is decremented. This can lead to _numActive &amp;gt; _maxActive although the real _numActive is &amp;lt;= _maxActive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix ensures that when an object is returned to the pool, _numActive is decremented in the same sync block.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12721850" author="psteitz" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2009 16:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in 1.5 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
